<body>
<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p><rs type="material" key="marmor">White marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> with <rs type="decoration">egg and dart moulding</rs> above on three sides (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.61</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.64</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.59</measure>).</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> (i) on central and (ii) on face to the right.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>i., irregular heights, ave. <measure dim="none">0.04</measure>; ligatured <foreign lang="grc">ΝΗ</foreign> in l.2; ii., <measure dim="none">0.03 - 0.035</measure>. Unusually for a sculptor's signature, the letters are not easily distinguishable from those on face ii.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date notBefore="0134" notAfter="0166" exact="none">Mid second century A.D.</date>
(<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>, <rs type="criteria">monument group</rs>, <rs type="criteria">prosopography</rs>).</p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<div type="textpart_section" n="i"><ab><lb n="1"/><persName type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Κλαυδία">Κλαυδία</name>    <g type="scroll"/>  <lb n="2"/><name reg="Μελιτίνη">Μελιτί<hi rend="ligature">νη</hi></name></persName>  <w>γυ<lb n="3" type="worddiv"/>νὴ</w>  <persName type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Τιβέριος" type="praenomen">Τιβερίου</name>  <lb n="4"/><name reg="Κλαύδιος">Κλαυδίου</name>    <unclear reason="damage"><g type="star"/></unclear>  <lb n="5"/><name reg="Ἄτταλος">Ἀττάλου</name> <space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <lb n="6"/><name reg="Ἀγαθεῖνος">Ἀγαθείνου</name>  </persName><lb n="7"/> <w lemma="ὁ">τῷ</w> <w>Δήμῳ</w> </ab></div><div type="textpart_section" n="ii"><ab><lb n="1"/><persName type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Ἀνδρόνεικος">Ἀνδρόνεικος  </name><lb n="2"/><persName type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Μουσαῖος">Μουσαίου</name></persName></persName> <space extent="3" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>    <lb n="3"/><space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/> <w lemma="ποιέω">ἐποίει</w> <space extent="4" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  </ab></div>
</div>


<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>i. Claudia Melitine wife of Tiberius Claudius Attalos Agatheinos, to the People.</p><p>ii. Andronikos son of Musaios made <supplied reason="subaudible">the statue</supplied></p>
</div>
<div type="commentary" n="notyet">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p><!--One of the series of dedications from the East Court of the Hadrianic Baths: <xref type="iAph">1184</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1185</xref>,, <xref type="iAph">1187</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1188</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1189</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1190</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1191</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1192</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1193</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1194</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1195</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1196</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1197</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1198</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1199</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1200</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1201</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1202</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1203</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1204</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1205</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1206</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1207</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1208</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1209</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1210</xref> ; all are by women, and apparently bore caryatids (see <xref type="iAph">1198</xref>). For the sculptor see <xref type="iAph">1189</xref> (=Reinach 69).--></p>
</div>
